Package com.intellij.psi.formatter

Class StaticSymbolWhiteSpaceDefinitionStrategy

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intellij.psi.formatter.AbstractWhiteSpaceFormattingStrategy
      • com.intellij.psi.formatter.StaticSymbolWhiteSpaceDefinitionStrategy
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    WhiteSpaceFormattingStrategy
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PyWhiteSpaceFormattingStrategy

    public class StaticSymbolWhiteSpaceDefinitionStrategy
extends AbstractWhiteSpaceFormattingStrategy
    WhiteSpaceFormattingStrategy implementation that is pre-configured with the set of symbols that may be treated as white spaces.

    Please note that this class exists just for performance reasons (functionally we can use StaticTextWhiteSpaceDefinitionStrategy with strings consisting from single symbol all the time).

    Thread-safe.

        public int check(java.lang.CharSequence text,
                 int start,
                 int end)
        Description copied from interface: WhiteSpaceFormattingStrategy
        Checks if given sub-sequence of the given text contains symbols that may be treated as white spaces.
        Parameters:
        text - text to check
        start - start offset to use with the given text (inclusive)
        end - end offset to use with the given text (exclusive)
        Returns:
        offset of the first symbol that belongs to [startOffset; endOffset) range and is not treated as white space by the current strategy or value that is greater or equal to the given 'end' parameter if all target sub-sequence symbols can be treated as white spaces
